%I A214555 #32 Jul 18 2026 09:17:50
%S A214555 495,549945,554999445,555499994445,555549999944445,555554999999444445,
%T A214555 555555499999994444445,555555549999999944444445,
%U A214555 555555554999999999444444445,555555555499999999994444444445,555555555549999999999944444444445
%N A214555 Subsequence of fixed points A099009 of the Kaprekar mapping, with numbers of the form 5{n}49{n+1}4{n}5, where d{n} means n-fold repetition of digit d.
%C A214555 Original name used 5(n)//49(n+1)//4(n)//5, where the symbols // denote concatenation of digits in the definition, and d(n) denotes n repetitions of d, n >= 0.
%C A214555 Conjecture: Satisfies a linear recurrence having signature (1111, -112110, 1111000, -1000000). - _Harvey P. Dale_, Nov 23 2022
%C A214555 The given general formula for a(n) confirms the above conjecture. The formula would yield the fixed point 0 for n = -1, which suggests that the nonzero terms could be indexed starting with n = 1, so that the listed terms would be 5{n-1}49{n}4{n-1}5, n >= 1. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 17 2026
%H A214555 Syed Iddi Hasan, <a href="/A214555/b214555.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..165</a>
%H A214555 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (1111, -112110, 1111000, -1000000).
%F A214555 From _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 17 2026: (Start)
%F A214555 a(n-1) = ((100^n+10^n+1)*(10^n-2)+3)*5/9, n >= 1.
%F A214555 G.f.: (495 - 495000*x^2)/(1 - 1111*x + 112110*x^2 - 1111000*x^3 + 1000000*x^4).
%F A214555 a(n) = 1111*a(n-1) - 112110*a(n-2) + 1111000*a(n-3) - 1000000*a(n-4). (End)
%e A214555 549945 is a fixed point of the mapping for n=1.
%t A214555 Table[FromDigits[Join[PadRight[{},n,5],{4},PadRight[{},n+1,9],PadRight[{},n,4],{5}]],{n,0,15}] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Nov 23 2022 *)
%o A214555 (PARI) apply( {A214555(n)=(100^n+++10^n+1)*(10^n-2)\/9*5}, [0..9]) \\ _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 17 2026
%Y A214555 Cf. A151949 (Kaprekar map n'-n"),
%Y A214555 Subsequence of A099009 (fixed points of A151949).
%Y A214555 Cf. A214556 - A214559 (fixed points following other patterns).
%K A214555 nonn,base,changed
%O A214555 0,1
%A A214555 _Syed Iddi Hasan_, Jul 20 2012
